DriveControl - Class in org.rivierarobotics.commands
A command for active manual driving of the bot by a driver Perpetuated throughout the course of the period of the Scheduler's activity Retrieves control and movement object instances from the Robot class to use Requires the use of the DriveTrain
DriveControl() - Constructor for class org.rivierarobotics.commands.DriveControl
Initializes local fields with runningRobot instances of DriveTrain and Joystick (x2) Sets DriveTrain as requirement for this command
DriveModeSwap - Class in org.rivierarobotics.commands
Inverts the driving mode of the robot between arcade and tank drive Stored by the instance variable isArcade in the current running robot Only needs to be run once (hence InstantCommand which only runs once) to invert a boolean
DriveModeSwap() - Constructor for class org.rivierarobotics.commands.DriveModeSwap

DriveTrain - Class in org.rivierarobotics.subsystems
The DriveTrain subsystem, which consists of two DriveTrainSide(s) (left and right) Each side has three motors in talon/spark/spark orientation, each set being controlled together.
DriveTrain() - Constructor for class org.rivierarobotics.subsystems.DriveTrain
The default constructor which initializes both DriveTrainSides (left and right) Uses motor controller ID and inversion mappings from RobotMap
DriveTrainSide - Class in org.rivierarobotics.subsystems
One side of the DriveTrain, either right or left Comprised of talon/spark/spark, not a subsystem but in essence 1/2 of one
DriveTrainSide(int, int, int, boolean) - Constructor for class org.rivierarobotics.subsystems.DriveTrainSide
Constructs a DriveTrainSide complete with talon/spark/spark motors inverted and with brake mode set, and PID loop applied.
